headline: Tyson Foods (NYSE:TSN) Faces Ongoing Legal Challenges In Cattle Pricing Lawsuit
summary: Tyson Foods (NYSE:TSN) recently agreed to settle a class-action lawsuit for $83.5 million concerning allegations of price manipulation in the cattle market. Despite this legal challenge, Tyson's share price increased by 8% over the last quarter, a move that aligns with a general uptick in the stock market following recovery from previous declines. Executive changes and dividend affirmations in February also likely contributed positively to shareholder sentiment. These developments, alongside...
